Java Timer class fires one or more action events after a specified delay. will be useful for continuously updating and drawing our images.

actionPerformed(Action event e)

keyPressed(KeyEvent e)
int c=e.getKeycode();
if(c==keyEvent.VK_UP){
//do stuff (this is the up arrow key)
}

2 other methods
public void keyTyped(keyEvent e){}
public void keyReleased(keyEvent e){
can be used to set velocity values to 0 to stop motion after the key is released.
}

